      • instanceUnsafe

        public <TModule extends Module> TModule instanceUnsafe(RegisteredModuleType type)

        Provides an instance of the module type given (for Java interoperability).

        TL;DR: Java users -- beware! This function implements instance for Java callers, but unlike the Kotlin equivalent, provides no guarantee that a ClassCastException will not occur.

        This method exists to aid Java interoperability: the instance method cannot be used from Java as it is both inlined and makes use of reified generics. With this method, Java users can query for interface RegisteredModuleType instances.

        The reason it is unsafe is that there is no guarantee that the cast will be correct: if the type requested can be cast to interface Module then the cast will succeed and a ClassCastException will be given where the call is made (i.e. the function will return with no error until an assignment type is checked). With the normal (and safe) instance function, the invalid cast can be caught before the function returns and dealt with appropriately.

        Type Parameters:
        TModule - The type to cast the module as.
        Parameters:
        type - The type of of module to get an instance of.
        Returns:
        An instance of the module registered for the given module type.
        Throws:
        - When no builder has been registered for the type of module requested.
        - When the requested module can't be cast to the type given.
        See Also:
        ClassCastException, interface RegisteredModuleType, interface Module, ClassCastException
